President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. These include Todd Batta as Assistant Secretary for Congressional Relations at the Department of Agriculture, Maria Cancian as Assistant Secretary for Children and Families at the Department of Health and Human Services, Julia Atkins Clark as General Counsel at the Federal Labor Relations Authority, Victoria Reggie Kennedy as Governor of the Board of Governors of the United States Postal Service, D. Nathan Sheets as Under Secretary for International Affairs at the Department of the Treasury, Mark Sobel as United States Executive Director at the International Monetary Fund, Francis X. Taylor as Under Secretary for Intelligence and Analysis at the Department of Homeland Security, Juan Carlos Iturregui and Roberta S. Jacobson as members of the Board of Directors of the Inter-American Foundation, and Annette Taddeo-Goldstein as a member of the Board of Directors of the Inter-American Foundation. President Obama expressed his gratitude to these individuals for their willingness to serve and looks forward to working with them.